annotation.TEXT: I bet I'd get temporarily frozen (and possibly damaged) if a snowball hit me.
The blue goombas can be killed by a thrown weapon.
Huh. I wonder how I get down there? That passage is blocked by an ice wall on the other side.
Oh, hey there, Cirno! How's it going?
I'll definitely take the time to get HP-restoring power ups, though!
BGM: TH10 - Stage 2 - Path of the Apotropaic God ~ Dark Road
That was weird how my head got snagged on that ice block a few seconds ago. Oh, and no, I didn't use left+right to free myself. It was more like down+right in that case.
Huh. A reset door. I smell a P-switch nearby...
So, maybe this takes place just before the Extra Stage of Great Fairy Wars in the timeline?
Wait, what's this?
Huh. I'm surprised the stage music here isn't related to Cirno or anything ice/winter-based. Well, anyway, we've got these blue spinies to begin with.

Alright, the third hit did indeed end the phase! Also, I didn't get hit during that phase at all! (I guess I was lucky that she didn't use her ice stalagmites at all after the first two times. Those would be tough to dodge with the water wave shoving you around.)
Oh, actually, I could grab that "B" that's just to my right, but I think I'll grab the one back at the start first.
Oh, alright, so I guess this is like a fire flower.
Sorry, I didn't leave that previous typo on the screen for longer like I usually do.
BGM: Project Nite Festival - 9999
Yeah, it's a reset door. I just had to check.

However, unlike in Stage 6B, if you use this reset door, those nearby power ups reappear! (Actually, 6B might be the only place where power ups don't respawn after using a reset door. I wonder how Silver Scarlet did that...)
Happy Cirno Day! And, welcome back to the ⑨th episode of Touhou Mario! Now, I'm pretty sure most (if not all) of you know which level won in the voting results, but let's take a look anyway...
Wow, how many hits does this phase take?
Good thing I've been leaving "B"s behind, just in case!
Wheeee!!!
Alright, so remember this ballooning section? (And, yeah. I'll use the left+right glitch a bit here.)

That could be used to farm for point items here, but you can do this with most reset doors/pipes, because of the reappearing "R"-shape of point items near them. Also, I already have tons of point items, so there's no need for me to farm like that.
Change this "your" to "you're".
The Scarlet Devil
Meet the darkness
Whoa! Careful! Fortunately, I think you're less susceptible to being crush-killed while you're in a cloud than if you're ballooning.
Hah! Even a snowfall fired point-blank on me didn't hit me there!
An "R" and a "B". So, I guess we're still making use of this Spell Card power up, and that pipe would serve as a reset in case I screwed up too much.
Well, if there are any hidden goodies over there that I missed, let me know!
At least the B-cards are being produced by a generator, so I don't have to worry about this fight becoming unwinnable.
Gah. That sucks, and now I need a new "B". Good thing I left that one at the beginning of this area alone.
Strangely, I can't catch an ice block that I've just thrown, so I only get one shot per ice block.
Finally! Okay, I just went back and counted, and it took 15 hits to complete that phase! (That's way more than ⑨! What gives?)
Okay, that's good enough so that I won't have to deal with those bullets anymore.
Well, towards the end of the ballooning part, there are two power ups near a bouncing Chuck.
Is there anything further to the right?

Just wondering if there's anything hidden over here, but I'm not going to fry every block. (I wouldn't want to risk falling into the pit below the ice blocks and instantly dying because the custom block that bounces me up wasn't present.)

Interesting. That last ice-shuriken landed on the block near the springboard, and then walked off that block and fell. I'm guessing the ice-shurikens are spinies, and that the blocks here are Mario-only blocks, except for the blocks supporting the springboards.
Oh, what the heck? That one clearly hit the wave, since the wave went down, so why did the ice block still shatter?
BGM: TH06 - Beloved Tomboyish Daughter

Heh, and I still have my firepower. So, I guess that means I could come back here again if I lose my "B" power up later and wanted it back. (But maybe the other levels here also have "B" power ups. I don't know yet.)
-Practice start!-
Alright, so I guess I have to fry her. Also, the "B" power up fell through the floor... Also, Cirno's dropping shurikens (or maybe they're snowflakes or something ice-based).
Of course, I'll leave that "B" back there alone for now, in case I need it later.
What was that, a Snowball Brother?
Yeah, I think so, assuming I fry Cirno with the right timing, because she can't cause collision damage to me while she's flashing! (Icicle Fall Easy, anyone?)
Nope, it's a pit! Then, how are you supposed to get these without getting hurt? Or are they just a trap?
Yeah, now she's throwing ice blocks at me, and I've gotta get one to land on the water wave.
Okay, I'm hearing somebody kicking something nearby...
That's two. Hopefully, this will be like the other time I saw this custom boss and will only take 3 hits... If this phase takes 15 hits (or even ⑨), that would be ridiculous.
Insert apostrophe here.
Oh, there's a bunch of point items up here.
Hmm... Well, I guess this is where I'd've ended up if I'd used the left+right glitch to phase completely through the wall back there.
Hmm... Is ⑨ Frozen forest ⑨ replayable? Yep, it is. Just wondering.
And there you have it. So, vote for one of these levels, and we'll find out where I go next time!
I see a little bit of water over there, oddly enough...

Okay, she's getting serious with the ice now! And, there's this water wave thing that pushes me... Wait... I've seen this custom boss before. I don't remember which hack it was in, though... (It was Undine from A SMW Central Production.)
Okay, now for this phase, Cirno's down low and hitting me with snowballs. (So, those do both freeze and damage me, or freeze only if I'm still invincible from another hit.)
Of course, I'll certainly get damaged if I clip an enemy like that.
Ow. I need another "B".

Yep, so ⑨ Frozen forest ⑨ wins, as expected. However, I'm going to make a quick stop at Stage 3 first, since someone voted for me to do this, and I am still kind of hurting from that Mokou battle last time.
Whoa, just avoided taking another hit there.
I'm so thankful that I'm not seeing any evil homing bullets around here... (Oh, no. I shouldn't have said that. Now I've jinxed myself and there'll be evil homing bullets coming up, right?)
Nice one. OMNOMNOM. Maybe next time, I should recenter the camera while I'm on solid ground and not in the middle of a jump.
Shouldn't this say "frozen" instead of "freezed"?
Insert apostrophe here.
Yeah, only three Cirno images. If I added any more, I wouldn't have been able to make the video exactly ⑨⑨⑨ seconds in length. (Oh, but 3 is the square root of ⑨!)
It also took 15 hits to clear that phase, and now it looks like we're doing something completely different...
Ack. Yep, stomping her doesn't work (I just had to check). Did Mario's color palette turn darker for a split-second there?
Alright, so here are the remaining levels.
Alright, it's boss time, against Cirno herself! Oh, and it looks like there's something important enough to be worth mentioning in a text box here...
Whoa, almost prematurely collected that "B".
Bingo! Now, I can throw it back up at Cirno, and hopefully not miss...
Huh. How did my fireball not hit that duder (duderette)? Well, whatever.
Insert period here.
Huh. I can't normal stomp the blue goomba (but at least attempting to doesn't hurt me). However, spin jumping destroys it. Also, the spinies are slide-killable like usual.
Interesting sound effect. Also, it doesn't give me any HP. And, whoa! Those shots go fast!

So, yeah. If you're careful enough to avoid the Chuck and the other hazards every time, you can get 40 energy per reset door use fairly quickly. (And, if do you take one hit in the process, you'll still get a 20 HP profit.)
I wonder if that's another reset door... I don't see any "R"-shape of point items near it...
Subterranean trip
Bam! Nailed her that time! Okay, now the water wave gets faster each time I hit Cirno.
Man, the high horizontal speed of my shots makes it more difficult than usual to dig downwards...
Uh, oh. Could the strongest boss of all be up ahead?
Bad Apple!
Okay, I think that's all the farming I'm going to do here. Reimu will get sad if I abuse this trick too much, because it means that I won't be donating to the shrine.
Ooh, there's a Lakitu cloud... Ohhh... So that's how I was supposed to get those other point items without getting hurt. If only I'd known about the cloud sooner...
These fireballs work like usual on the enemies, too. (Man, why couldn't I have gotten this firepower during the main game?)
Alright, now let's head to ⑨ Frozen forest ⑨!
Wow. I've gotta be more careful with that left+right glitch.
Ooh, careful. I wouldn't want to destroy too much of the floor here.
Hmm... Before I enter that pipe, I wonder if I missed anything to the right...
So, let's just carefully grab these...
What, no "Beloved Tomboyish Daughter" here? Well, I'm sure we'll be hearing that later on in the episode.
Oh, did I just find a safe spot?
To be continued...
D'oh. I took a hit and now I've gotta backtrack for another "B". Good thing there's one near the reset door.
Peaceful waterfall
Uh, oh. The screen dimmed and Cirno sped up! I'm still sticking with my strategy, though!

And, that's it for ⑨ Frozen forest ⑨! So, it looks like this is going to be sort of like Hakurei Adventure Mission, where every level I clear will form part of the path that I need to reach my final destination.
Oh, wow. It's going to be tricky to take the top route here...
Also, I tried making a chart here like I've been doing for Super Marina World lately, but I just couldn't make it look neat without it taking up a ton of space.
Here we go!
And, over here, there happens to be a nearby reset door that's most likely intended for the next puzzle.

Well, this is pretty neat. So, these are just the flammable/inflammable ice blocks that are fairly common in hacks, which means no P-switches are involved. (The reset door is most likely there in case I take a hit before I've fried the necessary ice blocks.)
Wait, what's this? Am I going to have to take pit damage to collect these point items? Or, is there a floor down there that I can't see?
Ack! Well, I guess that spot wasn't 100% safe...

Likewise, I wonder how I'd get to that stuff over here... Maybe I'll find a P-switch that works on these ice walls later... (It's possible that the ice walls could be graphically changed brown blocks.)
Be careful not to accidentally collect this "B" right now...
